{"tid":2516824,"cid":5,"subCid":0,"title":"印度宣布批准5G測試　供應商名單不包括華為、中興","createTime":"2021-05-05T02:10:32.000Z","updateTime":"2021-05-05T02:42:09.000Z","uid":227801,"like":13,"dislike":0,"uniUserReply":9,"replies":[{"pid":"e48f38595ef648e447d24f5eee63d90d4dbdc27c","tid":2516824,"uid":227801,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2021-05-05T02:10:33.000Z","msg":"[url]https://ne<del><a href=\"http://ws.now.com/mobile/international/player?newsI\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=http%3A%2F%2Fws.now.com%2Fmobile%2Finternational%2Fplayer%3FnewsI&d=qHuNkoJYq05zO%2BFPSordKxZZVu6JdVYNpUv5YkkCXtQ%3D&h=6f736b46\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">ws.now.com/mobile/international/player?newsI</a></del>d=433603[/url]<br />\n<br />\n【Now新聞台】印度宣布批准當地電訊商展開5G網絡測試，供應商名單未有包括中國電訊設備製造商華為。<br />\n<br />\n印度政府的聲明指，在為期半年的測試中，公營及私營電訊商將使用愛立信、諾基亞及三星的設備，兩間中國設備製造商，華為及中興通訊未包括在內，華為未有回應。<br />\n<br />\n雖然印度至今未禁止使用華為及中興的5G設備，但傳媒較早時引述印度官員指，印度將在六月公布可信任供應商名單，屆時電訊商只可以向名單上公司採購特定器材，而華為及中興很可能被列入另一份禁止採購名單。"},{"pid":"565a9998dc1196e655e34f70efd2637491090061","tid":2516824,"uid":155095,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2021-05-05T02:14:32.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"https://i.epochtimes.com/assets/uploads/2021/05/id12918313-f81068b54d29cb244755076d07987fa5.png\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fi.epochtimes.com%2Fassets%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F05%2Fid12918313-f81068b54d29cb244755076d07987fa5.png&h=e0014d68&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"https://cdn.hk01.com/di/media/images/dw/20200619/350622692136849408.jpeg/yxbWYSPS4oVHz4oyk2g706H_ulcdPkIKPsIrKD7CKyg?v=w1920r16_9\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.hk01.com%2Fdi%2Fmedia%2Fimages%2Fdw%2F20200619%2F350622692136849408.jpeg%2FyxbWYSPS4oVHz4oyk2g706H_ulcdPkIKPsIrKD7CKyg%3Fv%3Dw1920r16_9&h=c2612a4a&s={SIZE}\" />"},{"pid":"14cb60a25af95db44ba2ddd27b5ac9454bc6cffb","tid":2516824,"uid":91397,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2021-05-05T02